header.gameNote: NEW YORK LIFE ACC MEN'S TOURNAMENT - QUARTERFINAL

videos.description: Louisville's Khwan Fore goes for the thunderous dunk but is denied at the rim by North Carolina's Garrison Brooks.
videos.headline: Fore misses huge dunk

videos.description: Louisville guard Darius Perry had so much confidence in Dwayne Sutton draining a 3-pointer, he already started running back on defense.
videos.headline: Sutton drains 3 with support from his teammate

videos.description: North Carolina's Coby White spins and somehow gets the circus shot to fall as he was fouled.
videos.headline: White spins and hits tough and-1 shot

videos.description: After Louisville big man Malik Williams throws down the jam, North Carolina's Garrison Brooks powers through the defense for the and-1 layup.
videos.headline: Brooks answers Williams' dunk with and-1

videos.description: Coby White and Luke Maye each score 19 points with Cameron Johnson pitching in 14 as North Carolina pulls away in the second half beating Louisville 83-70.
